President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster for the Pueblo of Acoma and ordered Federal aid to supplement the Tribe's efforts in the areas affected by severe storms and flooding from October 4 to October 6, 2017. Federal funding is available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures on a cost-sharing basis. Gerard M. Stolar has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the Tribe and warranted by damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.